text: North Tippah Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It joins with South Tippah Creek to form the Tippah River. Tippah is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "to eat one another", i.e. cannibalism. A variant name is "Tippah Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Tippah County, Mississippi
